        "title": "Policy: add secrets auth provenance checks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds a Policy 1.0 secrets/auth provenance category with redacted evidence and doctor/lint findings. Stacked after #81104.\n\n- Records secret provider/input provenance without exposing secret values.\n- Enforces `secrets.disallowInline`, `secrets.requireManagedProviders`, `secrets.denySources`, and `secrets.allowInsecureProviders`.\n- Adds auth profile metadata/mode checks with `auth.profiles.requireMetadata` and `auth.profiles.allowModes`.\n- Documents the new policy rules and JSON evidence shape.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: adds policy conformance evidence and findings for configured secret/auth provenance without exposing raw secret material, including inline secrets, unmanaged SecretRef providers, denied provider sources, insecure secret providers, missing auth-profile metadata, and unapproved auth-profile modes.\n- Real environment tested: WSL Ubuntu-24.04 source worktrees created from `upstream/main` and PR head `ac8f697003556d3a15f984eb7b7edbf4a076c024`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch: created clean detached worktrees for `upstream/main` and `fork/policy-secrets-auth-provenance`; in each worktree ran `node --import ./node_modules/tsx/dist/loader.mjs ./probe-secrets-auth-policy.mjs`. The probe wrote temp `openclaw.jsonc` and `policy.jsonc` files, registered the real policy doctor checks with `registerPolicyDoctorChecks()`, and ran the real doctor/lint path with `runDoctorLintChecks()` against a config containing a sentinel inline secret, an unmanaged env SecretRef, an `exec` secret provider, an insecure file provider, and auth profile policy violations.\n- Evidence after fix (screenshot, recording, terminal capture, console output, redacted runtime log, linked artifact, or copied live output):\n\n![PR #81974 secrets/auth provenance before/after proof](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-81974-fresh/pr-81974/pr-81974-secrets-auth-provenance-before-after-proof.png)\n\n```text\nFresh proof artifact: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-81974-fresh/pr-81974/pr-81974-secrets-auth-provenance-before-after-proof.png\nProof summary: https://raw.githubusercontent.com/giodl73-repo/openclaw/proof-artifacts/pr-81974-fresh/pr-81974/summary.txt\n\neEFORE upstream/main:\nstatus=0\npolicyRegisterImport=missing-or-failed\nimportError=ENOENT\nchecksRegistered=0\nfindings=0\nsecretLeaked=false\nfindingTypes=<none>\nok=false\n\nAFTER PR #81974 head:\nstatus=0\npolicyRegisterImport=ok\nimportError=<none>\nchecksRegistered=6\nfindings=6\nsecretLeaked=false\nfindingTypes=policy/auth-profile-invalid-metadata,policy/auth-profile-unapproved-mode,policy/secrets-denied-provider-source,policy/secrets-inline-value,policy/secrets-insecure-provider,policy/secrets-unmanaged-provider\nok=true\n```\n\n- Observed result after fix: `upstream/main` has no secrets/auth policy registration path, so no relevant checks or findings are produced. PR head registers 6 secrets/auth policy checks, reports 6 denied posture findings, and keeps the sentinel inline secret out of serialized findings.\n- What was not tested: no live external vault or credential provider was contacted. The proof uses local temp config/policy files and verifies the policy doctor/lint path plus redaction behavior.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm protocol:check`\n- `pnpm check:changed`",
